{{Infobox language |name=Ahwai |altname= |region=[[Nigeria]] |ethnicity=Ahwai people |speakers=15,000 |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Plateau languages|Plateau]] |dia1=Ndun |dia2=Nyeng |dia3=Shakara |iso3=nfd |glotto=ahwa1235 |glottorefname=Ahwai }} {{infobox ethnonym|aner andùn|bener andùn|indùn||Nandu}} {{infobox ethnonym|anyeŋ|banyeŋ|hanyeŋ||Ningon}} {{infobox ethnonym|kùʃákárá|úʃàkárá|ìʃákárá||Tari}}
'''Ahwai''' is one of the [[Plateau languages]] of [[Nigeria]]. There are three [[mutually intelligible]] dialects, Ndun (Nandu), Nyeng (Ningon) and Shakara (Tari).
Blench (2008) classified them as distinct Ndunic languages. However, that same year ''Ethnologue'' merged them as a single language.
