'''Old Costa Rican Sign Language''' is a [[deaf-community sign language]] of [[San Jose, Costa Rica|San Jose]], spoken by people born before about 1945. Along with [[American Sign Language]], it is one of the sources of [[New Costa Rican Sign Language]]. (Woodward 1991, 1992)
