{{blp sources|date= June 2017}} {{Infobox Jewish leader | honorific-prefix =Rabbi | name =Yechezkel Roth | honorific-suffix = | title =Karlsburger Rav | image =רבי יחזקאל ראטה.JPG | caption = פוסק | yeshiva = | yeshivaposition = | began = | ended = | predecessor = | successor = | rabbi = | kohan = | rank = | other_post = <!---------- Personal details ----------> | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | yahrtzeit = | buried = | nationality = | denomination = | residence = | parents = | father = | mother = | spouse = | children = | occupation = | profession = | alma_mater = | semicha = | signature = }} [[Rabbi]]''' Yechezkel Roth '''is known as the Karlsburger Rav.<ref>''[[Hamodia]]''. Sep/11/13. p. D17.</ref> He is the author of ''Emek HaTeshuvah'' 9 Volumes, Chezkas Taharah Hilchos Niddah, Emek Shmaatsa Gemara, Chazon Yechezkel on Drush, Mishpat Ha’aretz on Shmittah, Keren HaTorah Ribbis, Mai Chanukah on Hilchos Chanukah and other works.<ref>{{cite book|year=1994|script-title=he:עמק התשובה|trans-title=Emek HaTeshuvah|url=http://www.hebrewbooks.org/924|language=he|location=Brooklyn, New York|access-date=Apr 20, 2016}}</ref>
In March 2016 he was hospitalized after a [[Myocardial infarction|coronary]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vosizneias.com/236273/2016/04/13/brooklyn-ny-rabbi-yechezkel-roth-hospitalized-and-on-respirator-after-major-heart-attack/|title=World Renowned Posek Hospitalized, On Respirator After Major Heart Attack|first=Sandy|last=Eller|work=[[Vosizneias]]|date=13 April 2016}}</ref> He was mekadeish his wife a second time after he recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://matzav.com/rav-roth-after-release-from-hospital-is-mekadeish-his-rebbetzin-a-second-time/|title=Rav Roth, After Release from Hospital, is Mekadeish His Rebbetzin a Second Time|first=G.|last=Sitrit|work=Matzav.com|date=4 December 2017}}</ref> His wife Rochel Roth died at age 77 on December 4, 2017 after suffering a heart attack.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/featured/1418326/boruch-dayan-haemmes-rebbitzen-rochel-roth-ah-wife-hagaon-harav-yechezkel-roth.html|title=Boruch Dayan HaEmmes: Rebbitzen Rochel Roth A’H, Wife Of Hagaon HaRav Yechezkel Roth|first=Chaim|last=Shapiro|work=[[Yeshiva World News]]|date=4 December 2017}}</ref>
==Prominent students== Roth, who is in his 80′s, leads a venerated Bais Horaah in [[Borough Park, Brooklyn]], and is one of leading [[Poskim]] in the world today.{{cn|date= June 2017}}
After many years of living in [[Israel]], he emigrated to the US, where he eventually became recognized as one of the great Diaspora poskim.{{cn|date= June 2017}} Years later, he began dividing his time between New York and Israel, where he secludes himself for weeks on end in [[Meron, Israel|Meron]] in the spiritual shadow at the most famous for the [[tomb]] of Rabbi [[Shimon bar Yochai]].{{cn|date= June 2017}}
In 1972, the [[Satmar (Hasidic dynasty)|Satmar]] Rebbe, Rabbi [[Joel Teitelbaum]] sought a [[Posek]] with uncompromising spiritual standards to serve on the Satmar beis din in Boro Park. The Rebbe’s spiritual requirements were daunting. Roth whose brilliance in Torah is surpassed only by his staunch principles that closely match those of Satmar, was immediately approved by Teitelbaum. He dispatched messengers to Roth's home in Israel requesting that Rav Roth relocate to Boro Park to disseminate Torah, and Roth assented. Since then, he has lived in New York, and although he is not officially affiliated with any group, he has close ties with the [[Satmar (Hasidic dynasty)|Satmar]] community.{{cn|date= June 2017}}
Roth soon acquired a reputation as one of the most Prominent [[Poskim]] of the generation. He accepts the most complex sh’eilos from all sections of the [[Shulkhan Arukh]], responding in lucid, understandable terms. His piskei halachah are studied and analyzed in batei medrash l’hora’ah throughout the world, and some of his response to personal status and family issues have ended months and even years of halachic debate where other dayanim were unwilling to take responsibility for such sensitive rulings.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/headlines-breaking-stories/406977/tehillim-hagaon-harav-yechezkel-roth-suffers-massive-heart-attack-placed-on-respirator.html|title=Hagaon Harav Yechezkel Roth Suffers Massive Heart Attack; Placed On Respirator|first=Dov|last=Gefen|work=[[Yeshiva World News]]|date=13 April 2016}}</ref>
